- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.

a.title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptualVariable: A variable at the highest level of abstraction.

a.title: ― PhysicalSegmentLayout: Used as an extension point in the description of the different layout styles of data structure descriptions.

a.title: ― UnitType: Unit type is a type or class of objects of interest (units).

a.title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).
a.xlink:title: ― VariableCollection: Group of any type of variable within the variable cascade (conceptual, represented, instance).

a.title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalRecordSegment: Description of each physical storage segment required to completely cover a physical record representing the logical record.

a.title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationSeries: Ensemble of one or more statistical classifications, based on the same concept, and related to each other as versions or updates.

a.title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.
a.xlink:title: ― Level: Set of all classification items the same number of relationships from the root (or top) classification item.

a.title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept
a.xlink:title: ― ClassificationFamily: Collection of classification series related by being based on a common concept

a.title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.
a.xlink:title: ― PhysicalDataSet: Information needed for understanding the physical structure of data coming from a file or other source.

a.title: ― ConceptRelationship: Relationship between a pair of concepts in a collection of concepts. Use controlled vocabulary provided in semantics to identify the type of relationship (relation, e.g. ParentChild, WholePart, etc.)

a.title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.
a.xlink:title: ― DataStore: Collection of logical records.

a.title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.
a.xlink:title: ― Universe: Specialized unit type, with the specialization based upon characteristics other than time and geography.

a.title: ― LogicalRecord: Collection of instance variables.

a.title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].
a.xlink:title: ― ConceptSystem: Set of concepts structured by the relations among them [GSIM 1.1].

a.title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.
a.xlink:title: ― EnumerationDomain: A base class acting as an extension point to allow all codifications (codelist, statistical classification, etc.) to be understood as enumerated value domains.

a.title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).
a.xlink:title: ― IndividualMember: Distinct element that is not itself a collection (atomic).

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
